[p 
	"First of all, our Rules for Linux TASing require the authors to 
	[a class=intlink href=/MovieRules#UseMovieAnnotationsToProvideInstallationInstructions 
		"provide installation instructions
	]a
	". Since inbuilt movie annotations that should be used for that were only introduced in libTAS 1.3.1, and your movie uses 1.3.0, as the rule says, you should have posted all the setup steps in the submission comments. This wasn't done, so we had to make guesses on how to make your movie replay properly.
	$LF
]p
[p 
	"Second, your movie is clearly sub-optimal. 
	[a class=intlink href=/2368M 
		"We have a record
	]a
	" comparable to your run in the imposed goals. By simply looking at both movies and trying out things from Masterjun's run against your movie, I was able to easily save frames here and there. Here are the first few places where you lose time to bumping corners:
	$LF
